{
  "doc_id": "13057",
  "text": "Another study in Iran revealed the prevalence of dental fluorosis was 61% [CITATION_1] ,which is more than the pooled estimation of this review. According to a systematic review and meta-analysis in Iran, the pooled prevalence of dental fluorosis was 52.6% [CITATION_2] . The study conducted in Tanzanian sector of the east African rift valley among 1434 children in the age range of 12-18 years, the prevalence of dental fluorosis was reported as 85.3% for mild, 75% for moderate and 41.4% for sever fluorosis [CITATION_3] which is significantly greater than this review result.",
